1
00:00:00,240 --> 00:00:01,779
(One day in March, filled with the scent of spring)

2
00:00:01,780 --> 00:00:04,310
"The old man shouted."

3
00:00:04,960 --> 00:00:08,360
"Then, he leaned against the mast."

4
00:00:08,730 --> 00:00:10,959
"Through the line across his shoulders,"

5
00:00:10,960 --> 00:00:13,699
"the old man felt the strength of the giant fish..."

6
00:00:13,700 --> 00:00:15,929
"as it moved in the direction he chose."

7
00:00:15,930 --> 00:00:18,299
(He's amazed to find food even in a book.)

8
00:00:18,300 --> 00:00:20,369
- "'Please make it come up.'"
- What?

9
00:00:20,370 --> 00:00:21,509
"Said the old man."

10
00:00:21,510 --> 00:00:22,510
What has gotten into him?

11
00:00:23,340 --> 00:00:24,609
Is he reading a book?

12
00:00:24,610 --> 00:00:26,379
- Gosh, seriously.
- It's not autumn now.

13
00:00:26,380 --> 00:00:28,249
- Where are your manners?
- What's wrong?

14
00:00:28,250 --> 00:00:30,210
As you can see, I'm eating right now.

15
00:00:30,550 --> 00:00:31,779
- You're eating...
- The food for my soul.

16
00:00:31,780 --> 00:00:33,179
You even eat books now?

17
00:00:33,180 --> 00:00:34,949
You're promoting your new TV show...

18
00:00:34,950 --> 00:00:36,489
where you wear a wig...

19
00:00:36,490 --> 00:00:37,720
- and a fake mustache.
- What?

20
00:00:38,490 --> 00:00:39,559
I'm not promoting anything.

21
00:00:39,560 --> 00:00:41,420
I turned on the TV to watch an NBA game...

22
00:00:41,830 --> 00:00:43,589
only to see the screen filled with your face.

23
00:00:43,590 --> 00:00:45,229
- No, that's not it.
- What show is it?

24
00:00:45,230 --> 00:00:46,429
"Kang Ho Dong Neighborhood Bookstore."

25
00:00:46,430 --> 00:00:47,499
- No.
- It's true.

26
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:49,829
- No, you're mistaken.
- Wait. Hold on.

27
00:00:49,830 --> 00:00:51,229
Why didn't you tell us you opened up a bookstore?

28
00:00:51,230 --> 00:00:52,839
I would've sent some flowers.

29
00:00:52,840 --> 00:00:55,839
It's a bookstore located in Kangho-dong,

30
00:00:55,840 --> 00:00:58,509
the cutest neighborhood in the whole world,

31
00:00:58,510 --> 00:01:01,709
and owned and run by Hocrates, who is a disciple of Socrates.

32
00:01:01,710 --> 00:01:04,649
And Hocrates is not me.

33
00:01:04,650 --> 00:01:06,149
- Is that so?
- Is he Hocrates?

34
00:01:06,150 --> 00:01:08,519
- So he's a different person?
- He's a disciple of Socrates.

35
00:01:08,520 --> 00:01:09,719
Oh, I see.

36
00:01:09,720 --> 00:01:11,689
- He's into his own bizarre world.
- Is it your alter ego?

37
00:01:11,690 --> 00:01:14,589
It's like Ppakgu calls himself "Monk NewJeans."

38
00:01:14,590 --> 00:01:17,059
- That... Well...
- Hocrates...

39
00:01:17,060 --> 00:01:19,259
One that show, Hocrates is said...

40
00:01:19,260 --> 00:01:21,800
- to be about 2,000 years old.
- Really?

41
00:01:22,570 --> 00:01:23,830
- Who are they?
- Hey, guys.

42
00:01:24,200 --> 00:01:25,339
- Who are they?
- Hey, guys.

43
00:01:25,340 --> 00:01:26,769
- Who is he? James Dean?
- What's going on?

44
00:01:26,770 --> 00:01:28,069
- James Dean?
- Who is he?

45
00:01:28,070 --> 00:01:29,070
- Is he a TV celebrity?
- James Dean?

46
00:01:29,071 --> 00:01:30,140
- Who is he?
- You see...

47
00:01:30,370 --> 00:01:31,779
Watch our videos too, please.

48
00:01:31,780 --> 00:01:33,309
- Is he a comedian?
- Right.

49
00:01:33,310 --> 00:01:34,680
- What?
- Who is she?

50
00:01:35,210 --> 00:01:36,879
- Hi.
- His name is Jeong Gyeo Un.

51
00:01:36,880 --> 00:01:38,579
Are you guys the 34th batch of KBS comedians?

52
00:01:38,580 --> 00:01:40,149
- They must be the 35th batch.
- What?

53
00:01:40,150 --> 00:01:41,419
- You're comedians, right?
- What is going on?

54
00:01:41,420 --> 00:01:43,789
- Gyeo Un.
- Excuse me. Where...

55
00:01:43,790 --> 00:01:44,959
- Who are you guys...
- Let me ask you this first.

56
00:01:44,960 --> 00:01:46,459
From which school did you transfer?

57
00:01:46,460 --> 00:01:48,020
- Hi.
- Hi.

58
00:01:48,236 --> 00:01:49,835
We're from...

59
00:01:49,890 --> 00:01:52,560
We Do Whatever It Takes To Promote Our Regions High School.

60
00:01:53,160 --> 00:01:55,299
- Two, three. Hello.
- Hello.

61
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:56,969
I'm Pearl J, also known as Officer Pearl.

62
00:01:56,970 --> 00:01:58,439
I'm Jeong Gyeo Un, an officer from Yangju.

63
00:01:58,440 --> 00:01:59,539
- Oh, that's why.
- He's from Yangju.

64
00:01:59,540 --> 00:02:00,739
- That explains "Pearl."
- Yangju.

65
00:02:00,740 --> 00:02:02,269
- Yangju.
- Yangju. Right.

66
00:02:02,270 --> 00:02:03,339
- Yangju.
- Okay. Please go on.

67
00:02:03,340 --> 00:02:06,439
Ji Ho goes anywhere in Chungju.

68
00:02:06,440 --> 00:02:07,609
I'm Officer Choi Ji Ho from Chungju.

69
00:02:07,610 --> 00:02:09,080
- Oh, she's from Chungju.
- Chungju.

70
00:02:10,550 --> 00:02:12,349
I'm the Food Master of Gunsan.

71
00:02:12,350 --> 00:02:14,149
I am Officer Park Ji Su... Sir?

72
00:02:14,150 --> 00:02:15,419
- Did I do it right?
- Drop the honorifics.

73
00:02:15,420 --> 00:02:16,420
I'm an officer.

74
00:02:17,850 --> 00:02:19,319
Gunsan!

75
00:02:19,320 --> 00:02:23,390
Hi. I'm the Cutie Pie of Nam-gu, Ulsan.

76
00:02:23,644 --> 00:02:24,531
I'm Lee So Hee.

77
00:02:24,830 --> 00:02:26,499
- Nice!
- She's from Ulsan.

78
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,260
- She's from Ulsan.
- Right.

79
00:02:28,830 --> 00:02:30,599
They're not just ordinary people.

80
00:02:30,600 --> 00:02:32,299
They're the best PR masters...

81
00:02:32,300 --> 00:02:34,970
who are dominating the Internet with their viral memes.

82
00:02:35,310 --> 00:02:37,339
- You didn't know that, did you?
- I didn't know that.

83
00:02:37,340 --> 00:02:40,879
Are you YouTubers or civil servants?

84
00:02:40,880 --> 00:02:42,849
- Civil servants...
- We're paid by taxpayers, but...

85
00:02:42,850 --> 00:02:44,079
- Civil servants?
- Are you guys civil servants?

86
00:02:44,080 --> 00:02:45,619
- Of course, we're civil servants.
- They're like government officials.

87
00:02:45,620 --> 00:02:46,849
But he may not be one.

88
00:02:46,850 --> 00:02:48,589
- I am a civil servan-dol, - Okay.

89
00:02:48,590 --> 00:02:49,890
which is a blend of "civil servant" and "idol."

90
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:51,889
(We've never heard that word since the foundation of Brother School.)

91
00:02:51,890 --> 00:02:52,989
I'm like an idol star in my region.

92
00:02:52,990 --> 00:02:55,530
- You're into your own universe too.
- You're a civil servan-dol?

93
00:02:56,130 --> 00:02:58,429
- Just like Hocrates.
- His own bizarre universe.

94
00:02:58,430 --> 00:03:00,759
- He's just like Hocrates.
- What's with...

95
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:02,829
What's with those pearl accessories?

96
00:03:02,830 --> 00:03:04,299
- Gyeo Un.
- It must be famous for its pearls.

97
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:05,969
Do you always wear those?

98
00:03:05,970 --> 00:03:07,170
I always wear these accessories.

99
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:08,609
- Pearls...
- When you don't have a shoot too?

100
00:03:08,610 --> 00:03:11,009
That's right. Pearls really suit my personal color.

101
00:03:11,010 --> 00:03:12,379
- Oh, really?
- Unlike your name "Jeong Gyeo Un,"

102
00:03:12,380 --> 00:03:15,349
you look a little "tired."

103
00:03:15,350 --> 00:03:17,009
- Right. We also...
- We know...

104
00:03:17,010 --> 00:03:19,050
that you guys are all very famous.

105
00:03:19,450 --> 00:03:22,419
But I heard you were surprised to be invited to Men on a Mission.

106
00:03:22,420 --> 00:03:24,720
I was like, "I got an invitation that I can't refuse at last."

107
00:03:25,760 --> 00:03:28,490
I thought that it was really... I mean, there would be no more...

108
00:03:28,760 --> 00:03:32,229
I have never been on any TV shows before.

109
00:03:32,230 --> 00:03:33,799
- But...
- You need to be invited...

110
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:35,069
- to be on a show.
- Of course. I got invited...

111
00:03:35,070 --> 00:03:36,900
Ulsan and Gunsan don't seem to get along well with each other.

112
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,839
- It seems so.
- I like you.

113
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,739
- Right? I like you too.
- Are Ulsan and Gunsan on bad terms?

114
00:03:40,740 --> 00:03:42,339
- There's a conflict between them.
- To be honest...

115
00:03:42,340 --> 00:03:44,309
Our images overlap because of our similar build.

116
00:03:44,310 --> 00:03:45,510
- So I'm a little wary of you.
- Really?

117
00:03:45,910 --> 00:03:48,209
- Their characters overlap.
- They have similar images.

118
00:03:48,210 --> 00:03:50,049
- Their characters overlap.
- My gosh. So Hee is competitive.

119
00:03:50,050 --> 00:03:52,919
The fact that we have similar images stresses me out a bit.

120
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:54,819
- Were you overweight as a kid?
- Slightly.

121
00:03:54,820 --> 00:03:56,049
I was overweight as a kid too.

122
00:03:56,050 --> 00:03:58,250
Both of them were overweight as a kid.

123
00:03:58,890 --> 00:04:01,120
- Weren't you overweight too?
- So was he.

124
00:04:01,420 --> 00:04:03,259
- I've never heard that expression.
- He was overweight as a kid.

125
00:04:03,260 --> 00:04:04,559
- He's...
- He was overweight as a fetus.

126
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:07,759
- He's on another level.
- That's incredible.

127
00:04:07,760 --> 00:04:10,070
I was overweight even when I was a newborn baby.

128
00:04:10,470 --> 00:04:12,739
- He was a heavy newborn.
- Exactly.

129
00:04:12,740 --> 00:04:15,309
So Hee, just as you said,

130
00:04:15,310 --> 00:04:17,639
do you have a sense of rivalry with Ji Su?

131
00:04:17,640 --> 00:04:19,309
You can tell by looking at us both.

132
00:04:19,310 --> 00:04:20,310
We're similar to each other.

133
00:04:20,810 --> 00:04:23,009
I want to get as much air time as I can on this show.

134
00:04:23,010 --> 00:04:25,320
- Which grades are you guys in?
- Grades?

135
00:04:25,450 --> 00:04:27,679
- I'm a Grade 7 civil servant.
- I'm in Grade 8.

136
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:30,050
- I'm in Grade 7.
- Oh, I see. I'm in Grade 8, ma'am.

137
00:04:30,790 --> 00:04:32,319
(Nam-gu, Ulsan, scores the first point.)

138
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:34,189
- They're in Grades 7 and 8.
- A smaller number is a higher rank?

139
00:04:34,190 --> 00:04:36,029
- They're in Grades 7 and 8.
- None of you thought...

140
00:04:36,030 --> 00:04:37,859
it could be voice phishing...

141
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:39,629
- when you were invited to the show?
- Honestly, I was doubtful.

142
00:04:39,630 --> 00:04:41,799
I thought that the other three were famous,

143
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:43,600
but you guys might not know me.

144
00:04:43,900 --> 00:04:44,900
But...

145
00:04:45,570 --> 00:04:47,039
I heard that he recommended me.

146
00:04:47,040 --> 00:04:48,469
- Gyeo Un recommended you?
- Oh, that.

147
00:04:48,470 --> 00:04:50,809
- I have met her before.
- That's right.

148
00:04:50,810 --> 00:04:52,839
- We met on SBS' variety show...
- During a shoot at SBS,

149
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:54,339
- we met.
- We met each other then.

150
00:04:54,340 --> 00:04:55,950
So I helped her get cast this time.

151
00:04:56,610 --> 00:04:58,079
- Thank you.
- You helped her get cast?

152
00:04:58,080 --> 00:05:00,549
- How you got cast doesn't matter.
- He helped her appear on the show.

153
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:01,649
How did you feel...

154
00:05:01,650 --> 00:05:02,819
when you got the call inviting you, So Hee?

155
00:05:02,820 --> 00:05:04,989
I was unsure if it was really happening,

156
00:05:04,990 --> 00:05:06,289
but I accepted the invitation.

157
00:05:06,290 --> 00:05:07,659
People around me said things like,

158
00:05:07,660 --> 00:05:08,889
"Who are you to be on that show?"

159
00:05:08,890 --> 00:05:10,859
"Can non-celebrities also go on that show?"

160
00:05:10,860 --> 00:05:13,259
"Then I'll go on the show too." They said such things.

161
00:05:13,260 --> 00:05:16,699
Since I'm here, representing Nam-gu, Ulsan,

162
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:18,199
- I... Yes?
- What did your bosses say...

163
00:05:18,200 --> 00:05:19,939
about your appearance on this show?

164
00:05:19,940 --> 00:05:21,299
You need official approval, right?

165
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:23,510
- We report to our senior, right?
- Yes.

166
00:05:23,810 --> 00:05:26,079
It was written in bold letters that I'd be on this show.

167
00:05:26,080 --> 00:05:29,309
My boss laughed so hard when I submitted it.

168
00:05:29,310 --> 00:05:30,649
"Why would you be invited to the show?"

169
00:05:30,650 --> 00:05:31,950
(Her side project seemed so flashy that it made her boss laugh.)

170
00:05:32,680 --> 00:05:36,049
Actually, I came to this studio last year.

171
00:05:36,050 --> 00:05:38,389
Chungju Man appeared on this show before.

172
00:05:38,390 --> 00:05:39,390
- Right.
- Yes, he did.

173
00:05:39,391 --> 00:05:42,359
- Did you come here with him?
- It feels like my second time here.

174
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:44,760
- You must be less nervous.
- I'm used to being here.

175
00:05:45,700 --> 00:05:46,999
It wasn't long ago that Chungju Man came here.

176
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:48,300
- She's cute.
- That's right.

177
00:05:48,670 --> 00:05:52,999
I couldn't even imagine I would be on this show as a guest.

178
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,439
- How did your family react?
- So...

179
00:05:54,440 --> 00:05:56,639
They were like, "Why would they have you on the show?"

180
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:59,909
"You're doing a shoot with Ho Dong? Are you sure?"

181
00:05:59,910 --> 00:06:00,910
They found it hard to believe.

182
00:06:00,911 --> 00:06:02,850
Did Seon Tae give you some tips?

183
00:06:03,050 --> 00:06:04,949
Seon Tae? I bragged to him...

184
00:06:04,950 --> 00:06:06,579
that I would be on Men on a Mission.

185
00:06:06,580 --> 00:06:09,149
He said it had taken a long time until he was invited,

186
00:06:09,150 --> 00:06:10,349
complaining that I was invited so soon.

187
00:06:10,350 --> 00:06:13,290
(Chungju Man complained about the belated invitation on the show.)

188
00:06:14,020 --> 00:06:15,020
That's how he reacted.

189
00:06:15,021 --> 00:06:17,089
As civil servants, you must know this well.

190
00:06:17,090 --> 00:06:18,859
You have to make documents...

191
00:06:18,860 --> 00:06:20,229
- and report to your seniors.
- That's right.

192
00:06:20,230 --> 00:06:22,029
There are procedures to follow on this show as well.

193
00:06:22,030 --> 00:06:24,069
Can you give me the document you prepared?

194
00:06:24,070 --> 00:06:25,169
We're not just ordinary civil servants...

195
00:06:25,170 --> 00:06:26,340
Can you move aside, please?

196
00:06:27,870 --> 00:06:29,710
- So Hee...
- Watch me for now.

197
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:31,239
Whatever I do, you should laugh.

198
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,440
It's hard for me to keep my job.

199
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:34,309
- Did you plan something?
- I'll give it to you.

200
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:35,310
Okay.

201
00:06:36,180 --> 00:06:37,180
Okay.

202
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:39,579
You should laugh, guys.

203
00:06:39,580 --> 00:06:40,779
- You should laugh, guys.
- Okay.

204
00:06:40,780 --> 00:06:41,780
(Smiling happily)

205
00:06:42,420 --> 00:06:44,289
You don't have to do things like this on our show.

206
00:06:44,290 --> 00:06:45,290
(Throwing)

207
00:06:45,790 --> 00:06:47,119
That's good. Keep going.

208
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:48,859
(The fantastic chemistry between a civil servant and a comedian)

209
00:06:48,860 --> 00:06:50,259
- Sit down, please.
- Okay.

210
00:06:50,260 --> 00:06:52,199
- So Hee... What?
- You prepared a mime act for us?

211
00:06:52,200 --> 00:06:54,530
- You should face the camera.
- I guess she'll burn it.

212
00:06:56,430 --> 00:06:57,599
She prepared a mime act.

213
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,739
- There are 2 pieces, right?
- Yes, you have 2 pieces.

214
00:06:58,740 --> 00:07:00,369
- I need your hand, Soo Geun.
- Okay.

215
00:07:00,370 --> 00:07:01,370
- Help me with this.
- Sure.

216
00:07:01,640 --> 00:07:03,409
I'll hold one of the pieces in my hand.

217
00:07:03,410 --> 00:07:05,309
And the other goes... Flip your hand over.

218
00:07:05,310 --> 00:07:06,509
- Hold this piece.
- Okay.

219
00:07:06,510 --> 00:07:08,439
I'm touching the tip of my nose. Can I touch your nose lightly?

220
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:09,579
Go ahead and touch it.

221
00:07:09,580 --> 00:07:10,580
It's soft.

222
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:12,250
- Where did it go?
- Open your hand.

223
00:07:12,650 --> 00:07:14,149
(The piece of tissue disappeared.)

224
00:07:14,150 --> 00:07:15,549
- Then what?
- Then...

225
00:07:15,550 --> 00:07:16,550
What do you think will happen?

226
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:18,320
(The tissue was moved into Soo Geun's hand.)

227
00:07:18,321 --> 00:07:19,390
- What happened?
- What was that?

228
00:07:20,090 --> 00:07:22,360
- What? She's like Choi Hyun Woo.
- That was amazing.

229
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:23,629
What was that?

230
00:07:23,630 --> 00:07:25,089
She's like Choi Hyun Woo of Ulsan.

231
00:07:25,090 --> 00:07:26,099
I couldn't keep up with her movements.

232
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,100
(She cleans up thoroughly after the performance.)

233
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:28,100
That was amazing, So Hee.

234
00:07:28,101 --> 00:07:29,199
She's so nice as a civil servant.

235
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:30,469
She picked up the tissues.

236
00:07:30,470 --> 00:07:32,069
- Right.
- So Hee, did you...

237
00:07:32,070 --> 00:07:33,399
prepare this performance in Nam-gu, Ulsan?

238
00:07:33,400 --> 00:07:34,400
I had to prepare something to show you.

239
00:07:34,401 --> 00:07:36,410
- You didn't have to do that...
- Give me a round of applause.

240
00:07:37,840 --> 00:07:39,039
- Don't feel pressured.
- Can I go back in?

241
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:40,079
- I mean...
- You may sit down now.

242
00:07:40,080 --> 00:07:41,379
You are a civil servant, right?

243
00:07:41,380 --> 00:07:42,380
Yes, I am.

244
00:07:42,580 --> 00:07:44,909
You look like you tried out for the comedian recruitment last year.

245
00:07:44,910 --> 00:07:46,449
- I bet she tried out several times.
- It's been 5 years. I'm in Grade 7.

246
00:07:46,450 --> 00:07:48,179
Yesterday, at home,

247
00:07:48,180 --> 00:07:50,189
you must have imagined how you would do on the show.

248
00:07:50,190 --> 00:07:51,849
- I was really nervous.
- Did your performance...

249
00:07:51,850 --> 00:07:53,619
go as well as you expected or not?

250
00:07:53,620 --> 00:07:55,289
- It went really well.
- It went well?

251
00:07:55,290 --> 00:07:57,159
- Oh, it went well?
- It went really well.

252
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:59,059
First, Soo Geun played along with me when I made this move.

253
00:07:59,060 --> 00:08:00,199
- Right.
- That was unexpected.

254
00:08:00,200 --> 00:08:01,229
- He pulled her toward him.
- Right.

255
00:08:01,230 --> 00:08:03,130
I heard that our staff...

256
00:08:03,370 --> 00:08:06,039
told her she didn't have to do it.

257
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,040
Really?

258
00:08:07,170 --> 00:08:09,139
- They said...
- Showcasing a special talent?

259
00:08:09,140 --> 00:08:10,609
- she didn't have to do anything...
- You don't have to feel pressured.

260
00:08:10,610 --> 00:08:12,179
like showcasing her special talent.

261
00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:14,579
- But she insisted on doing it.
- Right.

262
00:08:14,580 --> 00:08:17,150
- I see.
- So Hee, can you do...

263
00:08:17,910 --> 00:08:19,219
- any celebrity impressions?
- Don't expect that from me.

264
00:08:19,220 --> 00:08:20,380
Like I said, I'm just a civil servant.

265
00:08:22,690 --> 00:08:24,149
- Let's move on.
- You're claiming that...

266
00:08:24,150 --> 00:08:25,959
- right after your magic act?
- That's her excuse...

267
00:08:25,960 --> 00:08:27,959
whenever she's in a pickle. But she prepared the magic act.

268
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:30,259
The transfer form to Men on a Mission.

269
00:08:30,260 --> 00:08:31,429
- Names.
- That was funny.

270
00:08:31,430 --> 00:08:34,260
Park Ji Su, Lee So Hee, Jeong Gyeo Un, and Choi Ji Ho.

271
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:36,000
Welcome!

272
00:08:36,670 --> 00:08:39,169
- Welcome!
- The four of them wrote...

273
00:08:39,170 --> 00:08:42,339
the thing that they had in common.

274
00:08:42,340 --> 00:08:45,139
And they wrote, "The next Chungju Man."

275
00:08:45,140 --> 00:08:46,409
- That's true.
- They're famous, just like him.

276
00:08:46,410 --> 00:08:49,609
- Chungju Man...
- You are who you are today...

277
00:08:49,610 --> 00:08:52,549
thanks to what Chungju Man achieved...

278
00:08:52,550 --> 00:08:54,950
- He had a great influence.
- That's right.

279
00:08:55,050 --> 00:08:57,849
From a civil servant's perspective,

280
00:08:57,850 --> 00:08:59,220
what does Chungju Man mean?

281
00:08:59,860 --> 00:09:02,230
Chungju Man is like a deity to us.

282
00:09:03,330 --> 00:09:04,330
He's unapproachable.

283
00:09:04,331 --> 00:09:07,029
The title as the next Chungju Man...

284
00:09:07,030 --> 00:09:08,869
- is way too much credit.
- That's right.

285
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:10,269
- That's how great he is?
- We don't deserve the title.

286
00:09:10,270 --> 00:09:12,069
He's a deity to us.

287
00:09:12,070 --> 00:09:13,739
Ji Ho, you must feel different from the other three, right?

288
00:09:13,740 --> 00:09:16,439
I feel like I succeeded to the crown.

289
00:09:16,440 --> 00:09:17,709
- You're Chungju Man's successor.
- And...

290
00:09:17,710 --> 00:09:19,779
the crown is so heavy.

291
00:09:19,780 --> 00:09:21,410
I feel like my neck is about to break.

292
00:09:21,880 --> 00:09:24,649
As Seon Tae quit his job as a civil servant,

293
00:09:24,650 --> 00:09:27,519
the subscriber count of Chungju's YouTube channel decreased a bit.

294
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:28,579
Not just a bit.

295
00:09:28,580 --> 00:09:30,149
- And that...
- As many as Chungju residents.

296
00:09:30,150 --> 00:09:32,059
- You must be under great pressure.
- Right.

297
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:33,420
Yes, indeed. That's why...

298
00:09:33,920 --> 00:09:37,929
It killed me to watch our channel we built together fall apart.

299
00:09:37,930 --> 00:09:41,030
- As if your kingdom was crumbling.
- Right. I'm on the edge of a cliff.

300
00:09:41,330 --> 00:09:44,169
(As Chungju Man left, Chungju's YouTube channel took a downturn.)

301
00:09:44,170 --> 00:09:46,069
I didn't know what to do. But while watching YouTube videos,

302
00:09:46,070 --> 00:09:48,499
the YouTube algorithm led me to the perfect video.

303
00:09:48,500 --> 00:09:50,039
As if it knew what I was going through,

304
00:09:50,040 --> 00:09:51,540
it led me to a clip from "The Slave Hunters."

305
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:54,840
- Oh, "The Slave Hunters?"
- It was similar to my situation.

306
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:57,510
- I decided to make a parody video.
- I see.

307
00:09:57,710 --> 00:09:59,319
So I dressed up like the character by myself.

308
00:09:59,320 --> 00:10:01,049
- That's the one.
- This video is really funny.

309
00:10:01,050 --> 00:10:02,219
I edited the video by myself too.

310
00:10:02,220 --> 00:10:03,750
- She made this video?
- Yes.

311
00:10:04,290 --> 00:10:05,689
- Is this the video Ji Ho made?
- A parody of "The Slave Hunters."

312
00:10:05,690 --> 00:10:06,960
How were you feeling while acting?

313
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:09,430
- It's hard to recognize her.
- She'll say the lines too. Right.

314
00:10:09,830 --> 00:10:11,189
- This video went viral, apparently.
- Yes.

315
00:10:11,190 --> 00:10:12,660
By the way, those side dishes look amazing.

316
00:10:14,630 --> 00:10:15,729
They're too good for her to act sad.

317
00:10:15,730 --> 00:10:17,129
- There are too many side dishes.
- The side dishes look tasty.

318
00:10:17,130 --> 00:10:18,999
(She looks like she wants to flee like a slave in the drama.)

319
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,069
(It's as if she got on a plane, only for the pilots to bail out.)

320
00:10:21,070 --> 00:10:22,739
(- She's more like a troubleshooter.
- He picked the right successor.)

321
00:10:22,740 --> 00:10:25,409
She looks like she's crying,

322
00:10:25,410 --> 00:10:27,579
but she's actually laughing, don't you think?

323
00:10:27,580 --> 00:10:28,709
- Right.
- Oh, is she laughing?

324
00:10:28,710 --> 00:10:30,010
I see that you're smiling.

325
00:10:30,310 --> 00:10:32,219
I might have laughed a little bit,

326
00:10:32,220 --> 00:10:34,419
but I did get emotional while acting.

327
00:10:34,420 --> 00:10:36,649
Anyway, the video got positive feedback.

328
00:10:36,650 --> 00:10:38,419
- People loved that video.
- Indeed.

329
00:10:38,420 --> 00:10:39,659
She must be under so much pressure.

330
00:10:39,660 --> 00:10:42,429
Did that video help you prevent further subscriber churn?

331
00:10:42,430 --> 00:10:43,929
Yes. As soon as I uploaded that video,

332
00:10:43,930 --> 00:10:47,029
the subscriber count held steady at 751,000 for 10 hours.

333
00:10:47,030 --> 00:10:48,359
- And it hasn't gone down since.
- That's right.

334
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,629
- That's a relief.
- It went up a little, actually.

335
00:10:49,630 --> 00:10:51,699
Since you parodied "The Slave Hunters,"

336
00:10:51,700 --> 00:10:54,799
the subscriber count has been skyrocketing, as far as I heard.

337
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:57,640
Yes, it went up by 30,000.

338
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,540
So it didn't exactly "skyrocket."

339
00:11:01,340 --> 00:11:03,010
- It's hard to make that happen.
- I'll work harder.

340
00:11:03,180 --> 00:11:04,579
We have less than 30,000 subscribers.

341
00:11:04,580 --> 00:11:06,979
- It's just 1 video.
- Gaining 10,000 is really hard.

342
00:11:06,980 --> 00:11:09,049
How could a single video boost the number that much?

343
00:11:09,050 --> 00:11:11,049
Everyone else seems to share a certain sense of camaraderie.

344
00:11:11,050 --> 00:11:13,059
But Gyeo Un, I heard you were thrilled...

345
00:11:13,060 --> 00:11:14,960
- to find out Chungju Man had quit.
- Oh, really?

346
00:11:15,060 --> 00:11:16,530
It was bittersweet.

347
00:11:17,160 --> 00:11:19,800
- You seemed very happy.
- Is that Gyeo Un?

348
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:22,229
That's Gyeo Un. Gyeo Un has many faces.

349
00:11:22,230 --> 00:11:23,770
It was filmed in front of Yangju City Hall?

350
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,229
We watched this video before.

351
00:11:25,230 --> 00:11:26,899
- He parodied the coffin dance meme.
- Right.

352
00:11:26,900 --> 00:11:29,569
I parodied Chungju Man's video...

353
00:11:29,570 --> 00:11:30,809
that made him famous.

354
00:11:30,810 --> 00:11:32,009
(I'm rooting for Manager Kim Seon Tae's future.)

355
00:11:32,010 --> 00:11:33,580
- He's so talented.
- This is it.

356
00:11:33,710 --> 00:11:36,580
By the way, Gyeo Un,

357
00:11:36,950 --> 00:11:39,050
you did pass the civil service exam, didn't you?

358
00:11:39,420 --> 00:11:41,279
I passed the exam and was hired through the public recruitment.

359
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:44,719
You look like a comic book character.

360
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:45,859
Indeed.

361
00:11:45,860 --> 00:11:47,119
- Exactly.
- Like a character with that hair...

362
00:11:47,120 --> 00:11:48,390
- in old Japanese comic books.
- Right.

363
00:11:48,590 --> 00:11:51,829
- He has that hairstyle, right?
- There's always such a character...

364
00:11:51,830 --> 00:11:54,499
- in a Japanese comic book.
- Especially one about school life.

365
00:11:54,500 --> 00:11:56,129
- That's right.
- In the video,

366
00:11:56,130 --> 00:11:58,469
he declared himself the new king of civil servants.

367
00:11:58,470 --> 00:12:00,269
- That's right.
- That's the intention of the video.

368
00:12:00,270 --> 00:12:02,840
"I'm sorry to Ji Ho, but I'll be the one to succeed to his throne."

369
00:12:03,410 --> 00:12:05,979
- I showed my ambition.
- Okay.

370
00:12:05,980 --> 00:12:07,780
But the video didn't help me gain a lot more subscribers.

371
00:12:08,180 --> 00:12:10,509
- I gained about 5,000 subscribers.
- It's not easy.

372
00:12:10,510 --> 00:12:12,519
- You have such a unique character.
- About 10,000 subscribers...

373
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:15,419
If he walks around Yangju...

374
00:12:15,420 --> 00:12:18,890
looking like that, in a school uniform,

375
00:12:19,490 --> 00:12:20,959
- elderly people might think...
- Right.

376
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,390
- he's a delinquent.
- They'd think he's a delinquent.

377
00:12:23,430 --> 00:12:25,799
You shouldn't wear a school uniform from now on. Right?

378
00:12:25,800 --> 00:12:27,059
He looks like a rebel...

379
00:12:27,060 --> 00:12:29,130
- from a Japanese comic book.
- A delinquent or a boy...

380
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:32,470
- who never behaves as he should.
- A comic book like "GTO."

381
00:12:32,670 --> 00:12:34,939
- "Great Teacher Onizuka."
- He also smiles with his eyes.

382
00:12:34,940 --> 00:12:36,970
- Yes. He looks kind.
- That's right.

383
00:12:37,670 --> 00:12:39,980
- He looks cute.
- Many people say I'm cute.

384
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:42,080
My nickname is "Puppy Stung by a Bee."

385
00:12:43,110 --> 00:12:46,120
I'll be perfectly honest with you.

386
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:47,380
Here's what I think.

387
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:50,219
Right after Chungju Man left his post,

388
00:12:50,220 --> 00:12:52,489
he managed to gain more than a million subscribers.

389
00:12:52,490 --> 00:12:53,789
- A lot more than a million.
- Hello.

390
00:12:53,790 --> 00:12:57,760
(Chungju Man started his own YouTube channel after quitting.)

391
00:12:58,190 --> 00:13:02,270
(He hit 1 million subscribers in just 3 days.)

392
00:13:02,470 --> 00:13:03,899
Chungju Man left his post...

393
00:13:03,900 --> 00:13:06,599
and started his own channel. Then, he hit a million subscribers.

394
00:13:06,600 --> 00:13:08,369
The total number of views was eight million.

395
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:10,510
I also read the comment that Ji Ho left.

396
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:12,339
"Oh, Seon Tae. My dear Seon Tae."

397
00:13:12,340 --> 00:13:14,709
- Now Chungju Man could...
- Yes?

398
00:13:14,710 --> 00:13:16,509
- file a complaint as a resident...
- That's right.

399
00:13:16,510 --> 00:13:18,049
- because he's not a civil servant.
- That's right.

400
00:13:18,050 --> 00:13:20,479
He's not my manager anymore. I don't even know what to call him.

401
00:13:20,480 --> 00:13:22,290
- Should I just call him "mister?"
- Oh, you're right.

402
00:13:22,890 --> 00:13:26,090
Would all four of you quit if you have a chance,

403
00:13:26,560 --> 00:13:29,789
just like Seon Tae did?

404
00:13:29,790 --> 00:13:32,560
I have a feeling that Gyeo Un...

405
00:13:33,630 --> 00:13:37,530
- He's an ambitious man.
- It won't be long before he quits.

406
00:13:38,130 --> 00:13:39,799
It's written all over his face already.

407
00:13:39,800 --> 00:13:40,899
He'll quit very soon.

408
00:13:40,900 --> 00:13:43,970
The current number of our subscribers is about 35,000.

409
00:13:44,710 --> 00:13:46,280
- Did you say 35,000?
- Yes.

410
00:13:46,410 --> 00:13:47,779
- It's smaller than you think, yes?
- That can't be true.

411
00:13:47,780 --> 00:13:50,849
- Chungju has a million subscribers.
- Chungju is on another level.

412
00:13:50,850 --> 00:13:53,580
So I thought... I'm sorry to say this.

413
00:13:53,780 --> 00:13:57,089
But I thought the rest of you had more than 100,000 subscribers.

414
00:13:57,090 --> 00:13:58,349
How many subscribers did you say you had?

415
00:13:58,350 --> 00:13:59,989
What matters is the number of views, not the subscriber count.

416
00:13:59,990 --> 00:14:02,589
- Each got over a million views.
- The number of views matters.

417
00:14:02,590 --> 00:14:03,929
- Even so...
- The number of your subscribers...

418
00:14:03,930 --> 00:14:05,489
- is lower than 100,000.
- Even so, don't you think...

419
00:14:05,490 --> 00:14:07,059
you should gain more subscribers?

420
00:14:07,060 --> 00:14:08,259
We're nowhere near a Silver Button.

421
00:14:08,260 --> 00:14:09,300
- So what?
- I have a question...

422
00:14:11,270 --> 00:14:12,699
- So Hee, calm down.
- Calm down.

423
00:14:12,700 --> 00:14:14,499
- You said you were a civil servant.
- It's okay.

424
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:16,410
- Lee So Hee...
- You work really hard.

425
00:14:16,510 --> 00:14:18,010
- versus Seo Jang Hoon. Fight!
- Hey...

426
00:14:18,210 --> 00:14:21,079
- Why are you so mad...
- I wanted to meet him the most.

427
00:14:21,080 --> 00:14:22,209
- Why did you want to meet him?
- Why are you so mad?

428
00:14:22,210 --> 00:14:24,709
No matter whom I'm standing next to, I never look cute and petite.

429
00:14:24,710 --> 00:14:26,119
So I wanted to take a selfie next to Jang Hoon.

430
00:14:26,120 --> 00:14:27,419
- Take a selfie with me later, okay?
- Oh, I see.

431
00:14:27,420 --> 00:14:29,920
- I want to look cute and petite.
- That won't make a big difference.

432
00:14:32,150 --> 00:14:33,459
(Sulky)

433
00:14:33,460 --> 00:14:35,159
- She won't look cute and petite?
- Just...

434
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,790
- He's absolutely a thinking type.
- The score is 1 to 0.

435
00:14:36,960 --> 00:14:38,989
Why would you want to be cute when you're just a civil servant?

436
00:14:38,990 --> 00:14:41,899
- But anyone can be cute and petite.
- I have a question.

437
00:14:41,900 --> 00:14:42,929
How many subscribers do you have?

438
00:14:42,930 --> 00:14:44,630
- So Hee, what about you?
- Must I tell you that?

439
00:14:44,970 --> 00:14:46,270
- Well...
- How many does Nam-gu, Ulsan, have?

440
00:14:46,540 --> 00:14:48,070
We have 20,000... Which one should I tell them?

441
00:14:48,240 --> 00:14:49,240
- YouTube.
- I'll give you our best figure.

442
00:14:49,241 --> 00:14:51,439
We have 28,000 followers on Instagram.

443
00:14:51,440 --> 00:14:52,839
As for YouTube, we have...

444
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,180
- Then...
- What did you say?

445
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:55,609
You trailed off at the end there.

446
00:14:55,610 --> 00:14:57,380
- Speak clearly. What was that?
- Give them the YouTube figure.

447
00:14:57,510 --> 00:14:59,749
- We have 16,000 on YouTube.
- You trailed off at the end again.

448
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:01,479
- We have about 16,300 subscribers.
- You shouldn't be embarrassed.

449
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:04,190
- It's a great achievement.
- Your subscribers might be upset.

450
00:15:04,290 --> 00:15:06,259
- The number will definitely rise.
- Oh, right.

451
00:15:06,260 --> 00:15:08,119
- Really?
- After today...

452
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:10,459
- Thank you. Just 5,000 more...
- It'll rise when this airs.

453
00:15:10,460 --> 00:15:11,959
- No, just 500 would be amazing.
- That's not the point, So Hee.

454
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:14,260
Please subscribe "Nam-gu Ulsan Whale Broadcasting Station."

455
00:15:15,900 --> 00:15:17,000
I don't check the subscriber count.

456
00:15:17,470 --> 00:15:18,899
- You don't? Is it too large?
- No, I don't.

457
00:15:18,900 --> 00:15:19,999
- That's not the case.
- You have that many subscribers?

458
00:15:20,000 --> 00:15:21,000
I don't check it because it's small.

459
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:23,869
Earlier, Ho Dong said, "You gained a mere 30,000?"

460
00:15:23,870 --> 00:15:25,009
- That hurt my feelings.
- It hurt mine too.

461
00:15:25,010 --> 00:15:26,540
Why? We have only 30,000 subscribers.

462
00:15:27,180 --> 00:15:28,579
- You have more than we do.
- You have a lot...

463
00:15:28,580 --> 00:15:29,809
- if you have 30,000.
- Like I said, 30,000 is a lot.

464
00:15:29,810 --> 00:15:31,309
I said that it was a great achievement.

465
00:15:31,310 --> 00:15:32,450
Ho Dong knows nothing about YouTube.

466
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:34,219
But he said "a mere 30,000" earlier.

467
00:15:34,220 --> 00:15:37,449
Gyeo Un, do you have no intention of quitting?

468
00:15:37,450 --> 00:15:39,390
Do you? Are you planning to work for the city until you retire?

469
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:42,060
- I want to make a promise.
- Okay.

470
00:15:42,290 --> 00:15:44,259
What's the population of South Korea?

471
00:15:44,260 --> 00:15:45,359
- It's 50 million.
- It's 50 million.

472
00:15:45,360 --> 00:15:47,159
- It's 50 million.
- I'll quit when we hit 50 million.

473
00:15:47,160 --> 00:15:48,359
("Yangju Man to Retire after Hitting 50 Million Subscribers?")

474
00:15:48,360 --> 00:15:50,269
- When our subscriber count...
- So you'll hold out to the end?

475
00:15:50,270 --> 00:15:51,899
- You meant the subscriber count?
- When it surpasses 50 million.

476
00:15:51,900 --> 00:15:55,870
I'm sure you will quit once your videos really go viral.

477
00:15:56,610 --> 00:15:58,309
By the way, I'm pretty sure...

478
00:15:58,310 --> 00:16:01,280
Even though Chungju Man left the civil service...

479
00:16:01,580 --> 00:16:03,010
He came on the show not long ago.

480
00:16:03,650 --> 00:16:05,879
- I'm sure he'll be watching this.
- He'll definitely watch this.

481
00:16:05,880 --> 00:16:08,020
- He'll definitely watch this.
- That's why our guests...

482
00:16:08,350 --> 00:16:10,550
Each of them wrote...

483
00:16:10,920 --> 00:16:13,789
a short message they wanted to tell Chungju Man.

484
00:16:13,790 --> 00:16:15,320
- They wrote heartfelt messages.
- He will watch this, right?

485
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:17,659
First up is Ji Su.

486
00:16:17,660 --> 00:16:18,760
"Are you happy?"

487
00:16:19,300 --> 00:16:21,200
- She wrote, "Are you happy?"
- "Are you happy?"

488
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:22,730
I wonder what this means.

489
00:16:22,870 --> 00:16:24,930
- "Are you happy? Answer me."
- Okay.

490
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,870
- Oh, were you friends with him?
- "Happy to be a private citizen?"

491
00:16:28,070 --> 00:16:30,040
"Are you happy to be free while we're still stuck here?"

492
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:33,009
"Are you happy that your YouTube channel is a big hit?"

493
00:16:33,010 --> 00:16:34,280
- That's good.
- Awesome.

494
00:16:35,010 --> 00:16:36,479
(Lee Su Ji in civil service is even gunning for U-Know Yunho's spot.)

495
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:38,849
- She put on an acting performance.
- You see, So Hee...

496
00:16:38,850 --> 00:16:40,750
- So Hee, tell us what you wrote.
- So Hee wrote,

497
00:16:41,220 --> 00:16:43,689
"I wonder why he went to such lengths?"

498
00:16:43,690 --> 00:16:45,249
I mean, I wonder why he took it so far...

499
00:16:45,250 --> 00:16:46,790
to make a civil service channel a big hit.

500
00:16:46,920 --> 00:16:48,059
It must have been challenging.

501
00:16:48,060 --> 00:16:51,029
Because of him, acting silly is now the new standard.

502
00:16:51,030 --> 00:16:52,259
- That's true.
- Making ourselves look funny.

503
00:16:52,260 --> 00:16:53,499
It has to be provocative...

504
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:55,129
- to grab more viewers.
- That's true.

505
00:16:55,130 --> 00:16:58,829
She must've realized how hard it was when she actually made her videos.

506
00:16:58,830 --> 00:17:00,639
- That's right.
- You learn only through experience.

507
00:17:00,640 --> 00:17:05,370
(So Hee keeps pulling off such difficult tasks.)

508
00:17:06,980 --> 00:17:10,910
Gyeo Un wrote, "Is it warm outside?"

509
00:17:10,980 --> 00:17:12,579
Right. It can be warmer outside.

510
00:17:12,580 --> 00:17:14,349
- "Is it warm outside?"
- I see what he means by that.

511
00:17:14,350 --> 00:17:16,490
"I'd like to join you..."

512
00:17:17,150 --> 00:17:18,250
- "out there."
- "Help me get a position there."

513
00:17:18,520 --> 00:17:20,120
Watching his subscriber count skyrocket...

514
00:17:20,820 --> 00:17:22,659
made me feel envious a little bit, to be honest.

515
00:17:22,660 --> 00:17:24,189
But Gyeo Un, just as you said,

516
00:17:24,190 --> 00:17:26,260
until you hit 50 million subscribers...

517
00:17:26,400 --> 00:17:27,599
I won't quit.

518
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:29,470
You won't quit even if you hit 30 million?

519
00:17:29,900 --> 00:17:31,900
- Of course.
- You just hesitated.

520
00:17:32,370 --> 00:17:35,569
- He hesitated for three seconds.
- This will stay on the record.

521
00:17:35,570 --> 00:17:37,839
It seems to me that it's either one or the other.

522
00:17:37,840 --> 00:17:40,310
He will either quit soon...

523
00:17:40,880 --> 00:17:43,809
or run for the mayor of Yangju.

524
00:17:43,810 --> 00:17:45,749
- That's a risky comment to make.
- Indeed. We can't do such a thing.

525
00:17:45,750 --> 00:17:48,919
- He might do so when he gets old.
- Don't look at me.

526
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,849
- He asked not to look at him.
- I'm not planning to do so yet.

527
00:17:50,850 --> 00:17:52,489
Since you have your own unique character,

528
00:17:52,490 --> 00:17:53,759
- people won't forget you.
- That'd be amazing.

529
00:17:53,760 --> 00:17:55,459
- Last but not least, Ji Ho.
- People won't forget him.

530
00:17:55,460 --> 00:17:57,129
- Ji Ho wrote, - He's her immediate senior.

531
00:17:57,130 --> 00:17:59,660
"Why did you leave without helping me get married?"

532
00:17:59,900 --> 00:18:03,629
You see, I always act silly in my YouTube videos.

533
00:18:03,630 --> 00:18:06,100
I rode a bicycle while moving my hips to the sides.

534
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:08,299
- I got buried in the sand.
- Is this safe?

535
00:18:08,300 --> 00:18:10,039
- I swayed my hips...
- Last time, Hyeong Ah got buried.

536
00:18:10,040 --> 00:18:11,770
when every Korean could watch me dancing.

537
00:18:11,940 --> 00:18:13,780
Many people left comments that said...

538
00:18:14,140 --> 00:18:15,539
Chungju Man should help me get married...

539
00:18:15,540 --> 00:18:16,950
- before he left the civil service.
- That's right.

540
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:18,609
But he just quit.

541
00:18:18,610 --> 00:18:21,350
- That's why I wrote that message.
- I see.

542
00:18:21,650 --> 00:18:23,849
Each of our guests wrote a message for Chungju Man.

543
00:18:23,850 --> 00:18:26,619
Next, they wrote their key mission.

544
00:18:26,620 --> 00:18:28,219
And they wrote "Promoting."

545
00:18:28,220 --> 00:18:29,629
- Do all of you...
- Right, promoting is important.

546
00:18:29,630 --> 00:18:30,929
What are your exact positions?

547
00:18:30,930 --> 00:18:32,229
- What is it?
- Which department are you in?

548
00:18:32,230 --> 00:18:34,599
I'm with the policy and media team at Ulsan Nam-gu District Office.

549
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:36,729
- The policy and media team?
- I guess she handles PR tasks.

550
00:18:36,730 --> 00:18:39,540
I'm with the new media team in the PR department.

551
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:41,369
- It was formed last year. Yes.
- The new media team?

552
00:18:41,370 --> 00:18:43,039
- Was there always such a team?
- It's related to PR as well.

553
00:18:43,040 --> 00:18:46,379
- It was newly formed last year.
- Gyeo Un, which team are you with?

554
00:18:46,380 --> 00:18:48,679
I'm with the PR policy team in the PR department.

555
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:49,909
They all belong to a PR-related team.

556
00:18:49,910 --> 00:18:51,450
- They all belong to such a team.
- Yes.

557
00:18:51,550 --> 00:18:53,979
I'm with the communication and cooperation department.

558
00:18:53,980 --> 00:18:55,380
But I'm not in charge of PR tasks.

559
00:18:56,020 --> 00:18:58,490
I'm not part of the PR team, but the Hometown Love Donation Team.

560
00:18:58,650 --> 00:19:01,360
I'm in charge of the Hometown Love Donation Project.

561
00:19:01,490 --> 00:19:04,359
- What made you do the PR task?
- Exactly.

562
00:19:04,360 --> 00:19:08,199
The PR team is part of the same department as my team.

563
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:10,699
They said it was hard to find a person to be in their PR videos.

564
00:19:10,700 --> 00:19:11,900
- And you're talented too.
- Right.

565
00:19:12,070 --> 00:19:14,400
So I was like, "That's something I can totally do."

566
00:19:15,140 --> 00:19:16,210
She's very decisive.

567
00:19:16,510 --> 00:19:17,939
That was how I was in the election video...

568
00:19:17,940 --> 00:19:19,780
that was also aired on this show.

569
00:19:20,140 --> 00:19:21,209
- Right.
- That's...

570
00:19:21,210 --> 00:19:22,479
- when we saw that video.
- The election video.

571
00:19:22,480 --> 00:19:24,380
I'm the senior here. I was on it first.

572
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:25,909
- On what?
- True.

573
00:19:25,910 --> 00:19:27,419
- YouTube.
- She was on it.

574
00:19:27,420 --> 00:19:28,479
- I'm sure I watched it.
- Same here.

575
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:30,320
I'm telling you we watched Ji Su.

576
00:19:30,350 --> 00:19:32,419
Ji Su was already on a roll.

577
00:19:32,420 --> 00:19:33,819
She appeared on this show.

578
00:19:33,820 --> 00:19:35,059
(The video that gained her fans)

579
00:19:35,060 --> 00:19:36,159
It's election day.

580
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:38,160
- Your ID card, please.
- I don't have it.

581
00:19:38,590 --> 00:19:39,859
(ID card is a must!)

582
00:19:39,860 --> 00:19:41,159
(Excellent facial expression)

583
00:19:41,160 --> 00:19:43,069
My parents are old, so I need to help them.

584
00:19:43,070 --> 00:19:44,500
How did you do it?

585
00:19:44,700 --> 00:19:45,829
You made it so real.

586
00:19:45,830 --> 00:19:46,840
- Me?
- Yes.

587
00:19:47,170 --> 00:19:48,569
(Imitated HAMBUGGY, )

588
00:19:48,570 --> 00:19:51,170
(Lee Su Ji's alter ego, to promote Gunsan's food)

589
00:19:51,810 --> 00:19:53,180
I thought she was Su Ji for a second.

590
00:19:53,510 --> 00:19:55,580
- For real.
- She really pulled it off well.

591
00:19:56,010 --> 00:19:59,080
(Gunsan's flavors sink right into your ears.)

592
00:19:59,450 --> 00:20:01,079
- Amazing.
- Mul jjajangmyeon.

593
00:20:01,080 --> 00:20:02,080
(Gulping)

594
00:20:02,081 --> 00:20:03,449
(Gunsan makgeolli, pajeon, red bean paste bun, vegetable bun)

595
00:20:03,450 --> 00:20:05,420
(Spicy japchae, webfoot octopus, white glutinous barley)

596
00:20:05,850 --> 00:20:07,589
It sounds like Su Ji.

597
00:20:07,590 --> 00:20:09,119
It's Su Ji's song.

598
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:10,290
- Su Ji.
- Her alter ego.

599
00:20:11,030 --> 00:20:13,030
Anyone can tell it's promoting Gunsan.

600
00:20:13,060 --> 00:20:14,300
- For real.
- Even jjamppong.

601
00:20:16,730 --> 00:20:18,929
- This is...
- Didn't Su Ji do a shout-out?

602
00:20:18,930 --> 00:20:20,900
She did by commenting on the video.

603
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,069
Nice.

604
00:20:22,070 --> 00:20:23,370
(Influential to the point of getting the originator's shout-out)

605
00:20:26,940 --> 00:20:28,209
- What?
- That scared me.

606
00:20:28,210 --> 00:20:29,309
What's going on?

607
00:20:29,310 --> 00:20:30,909
- What is this? It's hilarious.
- Donate 100 dollars,

608
00:20:30,910 --> 00:20:31,910
- What?
- and you'll get...

609
00:20:31,911 --> 00:20:32,919
a full tax deduction...

610
00:20:32,920 --> 00:20:33,920
- and 30 percent of the donation...
- It's your job,

611
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:34,920
- right?
- money as a thank you gift.

612
00:20:34,921 --> 00:20:36,020
- Right.
- Isn't that about your job?

613
00:20:36,120 --> 00:20:38,190
That's the work I'm in charge of.

614
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,889
- Goodness.
- Cool.

615
00:20:39,890 --> 00:20:41,589
- Ji Su, you're really...
- Jjamppong!

616
00:20:41,590 --> 00:20:42,690
Look at the jjamppong.

617
00:20:42,990 --> 00:20:44,190
- The taste of hometown.
- That looks good.

618
00:20:44,660 --> 00:20:46,260
- It looks amazing.
- I can't watch it.

619
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:48,859
(Energized by eating jjamppong)

620
00:20:48,860 --> 00:20:50,370
Ji Su is good at it.

621
00:20:51,370 --> 00:20:52,939
(Thank goodness she didn't snort out noodles.)

622
00:20:52,940 --> 00:20:53,940
(A talent wasted on being a civil servant)

623
00:20:53,941 --> 00:20:54,970
(Gunsan's Ma Dong Seok)

624
00:20:55,670 --> 00:20:58,069
You must keep up with the current memes.

625
00:20:58,070 --> 00:20:59,739
(Meme Expert)

626
00:20:59,740 --> 00:21:01,640
Why am I reminded of Kang Ho Dong?

627
00:21:02,540 --> 00:21:03,909
- You're totally right.
- Yes.

628
00:21:03,910 --> 00:21:05,410
(Meme Expert and Meme Hunter)

629
00:21:05,550 --> 00:21:06,820
Were you okay after getting kicked by the horse?

630
00:21:06,850 --> 00:21:07,949
No.

631
00:21:07,950 --> 00:21:08,979
It almost gave me...

632
00:21:08,980 --> 00:21:10,390
- a herniated disc.
- Wasn't it smooth?

633
00:21:10,490 --> 00:21:11,749
How were the two videos connected?

634
00:21:11,750 --> 00:21:13,859
I thought Ji Su was kicked for real.

635
00:21:13,860 --> 00:21:15,120
- The horse.
- How did she do it?

636
00:21:15,460 --> 00:21:17,389
Because of how many views it got,

637
00:21:17,390 --> 00:21:18,829
I got a special promotion...

638
00:21:18,830 --> 00:21:20,929
- to Grade Eight.
- Really?

639
00:21:20,930 --> 00:21:22,000
Congratulations.

640
00:21:22,030 --> 00:21:23,230
To get promoted one grade?

641
00:21:24,070 --> 00:21:25,670
- That's awesome.
- Amazing.

642
00:21:25,730 --> 00:21:27,070
Editing that was tough, wasn't it?

643
00:21:27,170 --> 00:21:30,609
We have an officer who edits the videos.

644
00:21:30,610 --> 00:21:32,540
- They must be an expert.
- Yes.

645
00:21:32,670 --> 00:21:35,180
- That was incredible.
- You can say that I'm the actress.

646
00:21:35,440 --> 00:21:37,980
- Right.
- From what I see,

647
00:21:38,180 --> 00:21:40,349
Ji Su is different from the others.

648
00:21:40,350 --> 00:21:42,219
- She simply acts.
- Correct.

649
00:21:42,220 --> 00:21:45,149
Ji Su actually works in the Hometown Love...

650
00:21:45,150 --> 00:21:46,989
- Exactly.
- Donation Project department.

651
00:21:46,990 --> 00:21:49,529
It's a must for workers who do year-end tax adjustments.

652
00:21:49,530 --> 00:21:51,359
Donate 100 dollars,

653
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:54,229
and you get a full tax deduction.

654
00:21:54,230 --> 00:21:55,360
It's given back.

655
00:21:55,530 --> 00:21:57,869
And out of 100 dollars, you get 30 dollars as points...

656
00:21:57,870 --> 00:22:00,099
and can get the local specialty delivered to your door.

657
00:22:00,100 --> 00:22:01,499
Wonju also has such a system.

658
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:02,539
- It's nationwide.
- All cities have it.

659
00:22:02,540 --> 00:22:03,569
- Nam-gu, Ulsan also has it.
- Yes.

660
00:22:03,570 --> 00:22:05,269
By the way,

661
00:22:05,270 --> 00:22:07,339
not all PR teams do YouTube, do they?

662
00:22:07,340 --> 00:22:09,109
- No.
- How did it start?

663
00:22:09,110 --> 00:22:12,780
After Chungju Man's channel went viral,

664
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:15,420
- The local governments.
- did the other local governments...

665
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:17,489
- Right.
- suggest starting...

666
00:22:17,490 --> 00:22:19,119
- Try it.
- a YouTube channel?

667
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:20,659
We were already making videos...

668
00:22:20,660 --> 00:22:21,819
- when Chungju Man did.
- You were?

669
00:22:21,820 --> 00:22:24,460
We were making videos, but nobody knew about it.

670
00:22:24,790 --> 00:22:26,499
People say Chungju Man is first-generation,

671
00:22:26,500 --> 00:22:27,799
while ours is second-generation.

672
00:22:27,800 --> 00:22:29,099
But many local governments were making videos.

673
00:22:29,100 --> 00:22:30,329
So everyone was already making videos.

674
00:22:30,330 --> 00:22:31,769
- To promote the region.
- So Hee.

675
00:22:31,770 --> 00:22:33,369
Did the seniors recommend you,

676
00:22:33,370 --> 00:22:34,839
or did you volunteer to do it?

677
00:22:34,840 --> 00:22:37,669
I'm actually an extreme introvert.

678
00:22:37,670 --> 00:22:38,839
(A big twist)

679
00:22:38,840 --> 00:22:39,879
- But...
- Why does she...

680
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:41,110
sound like Shin Young?

681
00:22:41,540 --> 00:22:43,580
- She's giving Shin Young vibes.
- Thanks, I appreciate it.

682
00:22:43,780 --> 00:22:45,579
Nam-gu made a video titled "I'm Solo..."

683
00:22:45,580 --> 00:22:47,419
with 4 females and 4 males...

684
00:22:47,420 --> 00:22:49,379
- Nam-gu civil servants.
- I see.

685
00:22:49,380 --> 00:22:51,750
(The first woman)

686
00:22:51,850 --> 00:22:54,320
(Young Ja's cute charms)

687
00:22:54,560 --> 00:22:56,329
That video reached 400,000 views,

688
00:22:56,330 --> 00:22:58,729
which was way more than the number of our subscribers.

689
00:22:58,730 --> 00:22:59,959
I was Young Ja in that video.

690
00:22:59,960 --> 00:23:01,699
After seeing that I wasn't camera-shy,

691
00:23:01,700 --> 00:23:04,129
I was appointed to the department.

692
00:23:04,130 --> 00:23:05,369
After seeing you weren't...

693
00:23:05,370 --> 00:23:07,399
- I wasn't camera-shy.
- camera-shy.

694
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:09,139
And you have a way with words.

695
00:23:09,140 --> 00:23:10,169
I'm sure that played a part.

696
00:23:10,170 --> 00:23:11,939
- I see.
- If you were to make...

697
00:23:11,940 --> 00:23:13,309
a promotional video for Nam-gu, Ulsan,

698
00:23:13,310 --> 00:23:15,940
who would you choose among us?

699
00:23:16,010 --> 00:23:18,710
- I'm a fan of Yeong Cheol.
- Right.

700
00:23:18,910 --> 00:23:19,980
But I choose Jang Hoon.

701
00:23:20,620 --> 00:23:21,720
He's my top choice.

702
00:23:21,920 --> 00:23:23,049
Don't look at me like that, Yeong Cheol.

703
00:23:23,050 --> 00:23:24,919
(More of a fangirl moment than regional connection)

704
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:27,389
Isn't there a saying not to boast about your wealth in Ulsan?

705
00:23:27,390 --> 00:23:29,059
- Correct. In Ulsan...
- Right?

706
00:23:29,060 --> 00:23:31,229
- With Hyundai Motor Company...
- Many are wealthy.

707
00:23:31,230 --> 00:23:33,259
and HD Hyundai in Ulsan, they say many rich people live there.

708
00:23:33,260 --> 00:23:34,300
But I'm not rich.

709
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:38,729
- She's funny.
- So Hee,

710
00:23:38,730 --> 00:23:40,000
what's the parody video of "American Idol?"

711
00:23:41,170 --> 00:23:44,069
- That went viral.
- I'm a hot pink girl in Nam-gu.

712
00:23:44,070 --> 00:23:45,639
And I love it very much.

713
00:23:45,640 --> 00:23:48,339
Because hydrangeas are better than the others.

714
00:23:48,340 --> 00:23:51,110
(Promoting the hydrangea festival in Nam-gu, Ulsan)

715
00:23:51,510 --> 00:23:53,180
- You even mimed.
- I did.

716
00:23:53,350 --> 00:23:54,820
(Like this)

717
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:56,820
- She's good.
- What's with her?

718
00:23:58,250 --> 00:23:59,890
- What?
- That went viral too.

