As Soo Geun said earlier,

2165
01:12:08,640 --> 01:12:10,079
- the water temperature rose.
- That's right.

2166
01:12:10,080 --> 01:12:12,039
- So the skates moved north.
- I knew it.

2167
01:12:12,040 --> 01:12:14,350
- Really?
- Currently, Gunsan is number one.

2168
01:12:14,450 --> 01:12:16,349
- Then what's the lie?
- There is no festival.

2169
01:12:16,350 --> 01:12:18,580
That's right. There is no festival.

2170
01:12:19,290 --> 01:12:21,949
- There is no festival.
- Is there no skate samhap gimbap?

2171
01:12:21,950 --> 01:12:23,560
No. I made it up.

2172
01:12:23,890 --> 01:12:24,890
(Everyone fell for her description of the skate samhap gimbap.)

2173
01:12:24,891 --> 01:12:26,830
You described it as if you've had it.

2174
01:12:26,990 --> 01:12:28,189
I like all of those ingredients.

2175
01:12:28,190 --> 01:12:30,130
- What are Gunsan's festivals?
- You described it so naturally.

2176
01:12:30,260 --> 01:12:31,929
Time Travel Festival.

2177
01:12:31,930 --> 01:12:33,199
- Time Travel Festival?
- What's that?

2178
01:12:33,200 --> 01:12:34,329
- There are railways.
- That's right.

2179
01:12:34,330 --> 01:12:37,099
- You can feel the modern culture...
- That's right.

2180
01:12:37,100 --> 01:12:39,309
- through this festival.
- Is there the Jjamppong Festival?

2181
01:12:39,310 --> 01:12:40,740
It opens at the same time.

2182
01:12:41,210 --> 01:12:42,839
Jjamppong Festival opens at the same time.

2183
01:12:42,840 --> 01:12:45,480
Then there is the Artisan Beer and Blues Festival.

2184
01:12:45,810 --> 01:12:47,649
- Look at that.
- We make this beer.

2185
01:12:47,650 --> 01:12:51,650
That beer celebrates the 70 years of the Korea-US Alliance.

2186
01:12:51,720 --> 01:12:52,820
Okay.

2187
01:12:52,890 --> 01:12:55,859
It was picked as a beer for the official banquet.

2188
01:12:55,860 --> 01:12:58,819
The Gogunsan Island Trail...

2189
01:12:58,820 --> 01:13:00,530
is for pedestrians, right? It isn't for cars.

2190
01:13:00,760 --> 01:13:03,400
If you go there by a ferry...

2191
01:13:03,760 --> 01:13:06,499
and walk across the islands, it's 14km.

2192
01:13:06,500 --> 01:13:07,869
Will it open in May?

2193
01:13:07,870 --> 01:13:09,639
- Yes, it'll open in May.
- It'll be very popular.

2194
01:13:09,640 --> 01:13:11,669
- It's pretty.
- It's very pretty.

2195
01:13:11,670 --> 01:13:13,810
- It's so pretty.
- By the sea,

2196
01:13:14,310 --> 01:13:16,109
- the sunset is beautiful.
- The trail will open soon.

2197
01:13:16,110 --> 01:13:18,540
- Those are actual photos, right?
- It hasn't opened yet.

2198
01:13:18,710 --> 01:13:19,950
I thought those were computer graphics.

2199
01:13:20,150 --> 01:13:21,150
Okay.

2200
01:13:21,151 --> 01:13:22,449
(Gunsan has many attractions and food.)

2201
01:13:22,450 --> 01:13:24,050
It's nice. I didn't know such a thing existed.

2202
01:13:24,150 --> 01:13:25,849
Nam-gu, Ulsan, let's go!

2203
01:13:25,850 --> 01:13:28,050
- Han So Hee of Ulsan.
- Let's go.

2204
01:13:28,150 --> 01:13:29,989
- Give me a round of applause.
- Why? Will you sing?

2205
01:13:29,990 --> 01:13:32,259
(So Hee, let's go!)

2206
01:13:32,260 --> 01:13:34,390
Ulsan has Han So Hee, Lee So Hee...

2207
01:13:34,730 --> 01:13:36,160
- And Kim Tae Hee.
- Kim Tae Hee.

2208
01:13:36,800 --> 01:13:39,030
Number one. Nam-gu, Ulsan has...

2209
01:13:39,270 --> 01:13:41,929
Korea's biggest aerial bicycle place...

2210
01:13:41,930 --> 01:13:43,270
that crosses the sea.

2211
01:13:43,470 --> 01:13:45,199
- Number two.
- Yeong Cheol would know.

2212
01:13:45,200 --> 01:13:48,610
Some British royal artifacts are hidden in Nam-gu, Ulsan.

2213
01:13:49,380 --> 01:13:51,009
- Number three.
- Why are they hidden?

2214
01:13:51,010 --> 01:13:52,080
Seriously.

2215
01:13:52,340 --> 01:13:54,249
Hold on. If they're actually hidden,

2216
01:13:54,250 --> 01:13:55,920
- you shouldn't mention it on TV.
- Why hide someone else's things?

2217
01:13:56,080 --> 01:13:57,579
Why hide the British artifacts?

2218
01:13:57,580 --> 01:14:00,049
- You shouldn't mention it on TV.
- Unbelievable.

2219
01:14:00,050 --> 01:14:01,849
And people went through much trouble to hide them.

2220
01:14:01,850 --> 01:14:02,989
If you talk about it on TV...

2221
01:14:02,990 --> 01:14:04,820
Why did you mention it on TV?

2222
01:14:04,990 --> 01:14:07,829
- Hey, you should've kept quiet.
- They're the royal artifacts.

2223
01:14:07,830 --> 01:14:09,559
- This is bad.
- The British will want them back.

2224
01:14:09,560 --> 01:14:10,999
- Why hide them?
- They're so loud.

2225
01:14:11,000 --> 01:14:12,429
I'll move on to number three.

2226
01:14:12,430 --> 01:14:14,430
- I'll move on.
- Bicycles are in the air too.

2227
01:14:14,530 --> 01:14:15,569
- Number three.
- It's a mess.

2228
01:14:15,570 --> 01:14:19,139
In Nam-gu, Ulsan, even a whale can get its resident register.

2229
01:14:19,140 --> 01:14:20,240
That makes no sense.

2230
01:14:20,340 --> 01:14:22,270
- This is the hardest one.
- Only one of them is a lie.

2231
01:14:22,610 --> 01:14:24,379
- All three...
- You can't take its fingerprints.

2232
01:14:24,380 --> 01:14:25,839
Only one of them is a lie.

2233
01:14:25,840 --> 01:14:27,979
Are the British royal artifacts hidden?

2234
01:14:27,980 --> 01:14:29,079
- They're hidden.
- Did they get discovered...

2235
01:14:29,080 --> 01:14:30,219
and send back?

2236
01:14:30,220 --> 01:14:31,279
They didn't get discovered.

2237
01:14:31,280 --> 01:14:33,689
- They're on display.
- What are they?

2238
01:14:33,690 --> 01:14:34,849
What are the artifacts?

2239
01:14:34,850 --> 01:14:37,689
From Queen Victoria to King Charles Third,

2240
01:14:37,690 --> 01:14:38,920
the clothes and accessories...

2241
01:14:39,390 --> 01:14:41,259
of seven monarchs of the UK...

2242
01:14:41,260 --> 01:14:43,129
are on display...

2243
01:14:43,130 --> 01:14:44,530
at a place called...

2244
01:14:44,700 --> 01:14:45,859
the Jangsaengpo Cultural Warehouse.

2245
01:14:45,860 --> 01:14:47,669
- Are they on display?
- They're on display.

2246
01:14:47,670 --> 01:14:49,740
- Are they on display?
- I just said that they were hidden.

2247
01:14:49,870 --> 01:14:51,639
What if Beckham comes to find them?

2248
01:14:51,640 --> 01:14:53,709
They'll be on display from March to June.

2249
01:14:53,710 --> 01:14:55,109
- Isn't Beckham British?
- Yes, he is.

2250
01:14:55,110 --> 01:14:56,380
He is, right? I know that.

2251
01:14:56,580 --> 01:14:58,380
How did you obtain them?

2252
01:14:58,980 --> 01:15:00,950
How did we obtain them? Through legal means.

2253
01:15:01,210 --> 01:15:02,650
- Why?
- Are you sure it was legal?

2254
01:15:02,750 --> 01:15:04,849
- It was legal.
- Nam-gu, Ulsan isn't related...

2255
01:15:04,850 --> 01:15:06,819
to the British royal family.

2256
01:15:06,820 --> 01:15:09,890
- Only in Nam-gu, not entire Ulsan?
- It isn't related.

2257
01:15:10,260 --> 01:15:11,889
Have you seen the artifacts of the British royal family?

2258
01:15:11,890 --> 01:15:13,159
- You need to go to the UK for that.
- Right.

2259
01:15:13,160 --> 01:15:14,829
Instead, you can go to Jangsaengpo.

2260
01:15:14,830 --> 01:15:17,430
So why are the artifacts of the British royal family...

2261
01:15:17,700 --> 01:15:19,299
- in Jangsaengpo?
- For example,

2262
01:15:19,300 --> 01:15:21,669
did they come to Nam-gu historically...

2263
01:15:21,670 --> 01:15:23,469
- for some reason...
- That's right.

2264
01:15:23,470 --> 01:15:25,739
and leave behind the artifacts? Without such a story...

2265
01:15:25,740 --> 01:15:27,439
- There isn't such a story.
- No?

2266
01:15:27,440 --> 01:15:29,580
- If I remember correctly...
- What?

2267
01:15:29,710 --> 01:15:31,639
- This is strange.
- Don't try to be funny.

2268
01:15:31,640 --> 01:15:32,879
- I'm serious.
- There isn't such a story?

2269
01:15:32,880 --> 01:15:34,110
- No, there isn't.
- Soo Geun is flustered.

2270
01:15:34,210 --> 01:15:36,049
- I think number 2 is a lie.
- I think it's number 2.

2271
01:15:36,050 --> 01:15:37,279
So Hee has no story whatsoever.

2272
01:15:37,280 --> 01:15:38,949
- She just said they were there.
- Listen.

2273
01:15:38,950 --> 01:15:41,250
How would I tell a story about those artifacts?

2274
01:15:41,690 --> 01:15:43,219
- You could've told...
- She has no story.

2275
01:15:43,220 --> 01:15:45,589
- a story about the pirates...
- How would I...

2276
01:15:45,590 --> 01:15:48,459
- and a treasure chest.
- That's what I'm saying.

2277
01:15:48,460 --> 01:15:50,600
Perhaps they're from another country's royal family.

2278
01:15:50,730 --> 01:15:51,959
But she looks so victimized.

2279
01:15:51,960 --> 01:15:53,329
- There must be a reason.
- There must be a reason.

2280
01:15:53,330 --> 01:15:55,169
- Number three...
- They need to be registered.

2281
01:15:55,170 --> 01:15:58,400
- It must be symbolic.
- Jangsaengpo is known for whales.

2282
01:15:59,140 --> 01:16:01,769
- Whales...
- They must have numbers.

2283
01:16:01,770 --> 01:16:03,779
- That's right.
- There must be something similar.

2284
01:16:03,780 --> 01:16:05,909
Does the number start with one for the male whales?

2285
01:16:05,910 --> 01:16:08,249
No, it's 3 or 4.

2286
01:16:08,250 --> 01:16:10,750
- If you were born after the 90s...
- They were born after 2000.

2287
01:16:10,920 --> 01:16:12,149
The numbers start with 3 or 4.

2288
01:16:12,150 --> 01:16:13,519
The resident register means...

2289
01:16:13,520 --> 01:16:14,889
- that it has a family.
- It makes no sense.

2290
01:16:14,890 --> 01:16:16,859
It has a family. There's a whale museum.

2291
01:16:16,860 --> 01:16:18,290
Four dolphins live there.

2292
01:16:18,460 --> 01:16:20,329
Each one of them has...

2293
01:16:20,330 --> 01:16:22,189
- a resident registration number.
- I see. Dolphins.

2294
01:16:22,190 --> 01:16:23,659
We can get a copy...

2295
01:16:23,660 --> 01:16:26,270
- of their resident register.
- Dolphins.

2296
01:16:26,600 --> 01:16:28,270
The head of the household, members,

2297
01:16:28,400 --> 01:16:30,399
- and address are on it.
- Is there such information?

2298
01:16:30,400 --> 01:16:31,999
- Yes, there is.
- What if someone gets loans...

2299
01:16:32,000 --> 01:16:33,510
with their resident register?

2300
01:16:33,940 --> 01:16:35,639
- I don't know about that.
- They should be careful.

2301
01:16:35,640 --> 01:16:36,679
Will banks allow that?

2302
01:16:36,680 --> 01:16:38,310
- SH Suhyup Bank might.
- They might get dolphin food.

2303
01:16:38,680 --> 01:16:40,449
Hold on. Let's say...

2304
01:16:40,450 --> 01:16:43,220
they get a divorce like Sang Min or Jang Hoon.

2305
01:16:44,280 --> 01:16:46,490
- Will they need documents?
- They need to split the fortune.

2306
01:16:46,790 --> 01:16:47,989
They need to split the tank.

2307
01:16:47,990 --> 01:16:50,620
How would you know if the dolphins got a divorce?

2308
01:16:51,020 --> 01:16:53,259
They might be married. They might be divorced.

2309
01:16:53,260 --> 01:16:55,859
- Don't worry.
- How will you know?

2310
01:16:55,860 --> 01:16:57,130
There's no married couple.

2311
01:16:57,230 --> 01:16:59,530
- What?
- Mom, son,

2312
01:16:59,730 --> 01:17:02,000
and mom's sister make up the family.

2313
01:17:02,330 --> 01:17:03,439
So thankfully, that won't happen.

2314
01:17:03,440 --> 01:17:04,969
- I'm suspicious of number three.
- Right?

2315
01:17:04,970 --> 01:17:06,069
I don't think it's the resident register.

2316
01:17:06,070 --> 01:17:08,269
She said you could get a copy at the district office.

2317
01:17:08,270 --> 01:17:09,340
- It makes no sense.
- It makes no sense.

2318
01:17:09,480 --> 01:17:12,140
Hey, do you guys have resident registers for the otters?

2319
01:17:12,280 --> 01:17:15,349
- No.
- We see the whales as residents.

2320
01:17:15,350 --> 01:17:17,649
- Really?
- Number three is a good one.

2321
01:17:17,650 --> 01:17:19,819
Dooly and Go Gil Dong have...

2322
01:17:19,820 --> 01:17:21,449
- a resident registration number.
- Dooly has it.

2323
01:17:21,450 --> 01:17:22,589
- Really?
- Dooly is the same age as me.

2324
01:17:22,590 --> 01:17:24,819
Do you need to pay to get a copy of the resident register?

2325
01:17:24,820 --> 01:17:26,160
Do you need to pay 40 cents? How much is it?

2326
01:17:26,890 --> 01:17:29,460
- Maybe they prefer a snack.
- This is driving me crazy.

2327
01:17:29,660 --> 01:17:31,499
- What are you saying?
- You don't need to pay, I think.

2328
01:17:31,500 --> 01:17:33,670
How much does it cost to ride the aerial bicycle?

2329
01:17:33,800 --> 01:17:34,829
Five dollars.

2330
01:17:34,830 --> 01:17:36,239
- Have you ridden it?
- Yes, I have.

2331
01:17:36,240 --> 01:17:37,969
It's very high up.

2332
01:17:37,970 --> 01:17:39,739
It's about 11m above the ground.

2333
01:17:39,740 --> 01:17:41,970
I'm sorry, but what's an aerial bicycle?

2334
01:17:42,310 --> 01:17:43,409
Haven't you heard of it?

2335
01:17:43,410 --> 01:17:45,509
- They're bicycles in the air.
- There are cables in the air.

2336
01:17:45,510 --> 01:17:47,249
You just need to pedal to go forward.

2337
01:17:47,250 --> 01:17:49,779
- Are they actual bicycles?
- The aerial bicycle place is...

2338
01:17:49,780 --> 01:17:51,679
- at the Jangsaengpo Park, right?
- Yes! You know it.

2339
01:17:51,680 --> 01:17:53,089
- There is an aerial bicycle place.
- So...

2340
01:17:53,090 --> 01:17:55,519
- We know one is true.
- Couples usually ride it.

2341
01:17:55,520 --> 01:17:57,420
- Two people ride it.
- This one is true.

2342
01:17:57,560 --> 01:17:59,559
- Did you see it?
- Does it cross the sea?

2343
01:17:59,560 --> 01:18:00,959
Yes. Jangsaengpo is by the sea.

2344
01:18:00,960 --> 01:18:02,929
It crosses the sea.

2345
01:18:02,930 --> 01:18:05,529
The other team went to the aerial bicycle place...

2346
01:18:05,530 --> 01:18:08,469
and my team went to the Whale Museum.

2347
01:18:08,470 --> 01:18:09,899
- I remember the place.
- It exists.

2348
01:18:09,900 --> 01:18:12,039
There was a monorail for the aerial bicycle.

2349
01:18:12,040 --> 01:18:13,539
- I...
- It crosses the sea.

2350
01:18:13,540 --> 01:18:15,469
- Okay. Let's go.
- Okay.

2351
01:18:15,470 --> 01:18:16,679
(It's time to choose the lie.)

2352
01:18:16,680 --> 01:18:18,439
The aerial bicycle.

2353
01:18:18,440 --> 01:18:21,509
Who thinks the aerial bicycle is a lie? In 1, 2, 3.

2354
01:18:21,510 --> 01:18:23,179
- I trust Yeong Cheol.
- Yeong Cheol has seen it.

2355
01:18:23,180 --> 01:18:25,219
- Kyung Hoon mentioned it too.
- There's no need to lie about that.

2356
01:18:25,220 --> 01:18:28,849
British royal family's artifacts. Who thinks this one a lie?

2357
01:18:28,850 --> 01:18:30,119
In 1, 2, 3.

2358
01:18:30,120 --> 01:18:31,760
- It's this one.
- It sounds a bit...

2359
01:18:31,860 --> 01:18:33,329
They could be from another country.

2360
01:18:33,330 --> 01:18:34,989
- Not the UK.
- Not the UK.

2361
01:18:34,990 --> 01:18:37,529
The last one, number three, the whales' resident register.

2362
01:18:37,530 --> 01:18:39,229
Who thinks it's a nonsense?

2363
01:18:39,230 --> 01:18:40,400
In 1, 2, 3.

2364
01:18:40,670 --> 01:18:42,569
I don't think it's the resident register.

2365
01:18:42,570 --> 01:18:44,299
Numbers 2 and 3 are confusing.

2366
01:18:44,300 --> 01:18:45,569
- Which one will it be?
- Are you guys done?

2367
01:18:45,570 --> 01:18:46,640
- Yes.
- The answer is...

2368
01:18:47,370 --> 01:18:49,140
(Nam-gu, Ulsan, doesn't have a story about the UK.)

2369
01:18:49,540 --> 01:18:51,180
(Whales don't have the resident register.)

2370
01:18:52,280 --> 01:18:53,280
number one.

2371
01:18:54,150 --> 01:18:55,550
- No one got it right.
- What's wrong with Yeong Cheol?

2372
01:18:55,850 --> 01:18:57,449
(Shocked)

2373
01:18:57,450 --> 01:18:58,549
- No one got it right.
- What's wrong with Yeong Cheol?

2374
01:18:58,550 --> 01:19:00,219
- I think I've seen it.
- What's wrong with you?

2375
01:19:00,220 --> 01:19:01,789
- You are from Ulsan.
- What's wrong with you?

2376
01:19:01,790 --> 01:19:04,290
- For goodness' sake.
- What's wrong with you?

2377
01:19:04,460 --> 01:19:06,659
- Thanks, Yeong Cheol.
- I think I've seen it.

2378
01:19:06,660 --> 01:19:08,359
- Thanks, Yeong Cheol.
- You said you've been there.

2379
01:19:08,360 --> 01:19:09,659
- It wasn't a guess.
- Hey.

2380
01:19:09,660 --> 01:19:12,360
- I...
- You said it crossed the sea.

2381
01:19:12,430 --> 01:19:14,229
- I rode something.
- You said you rode it.

2382
01:19:14,230 --> 01:19:15,929
- I go to Ulsan.
- Was it...

2383
01:19:15,930 --> 01:19:17,039
Was it a monorail?

2384
01:19:17,040 --> 01:19:18,869
- I mean...
- There's a monorail too.

2385
01:19:18,870 --> 01:19:20,639
- I guess it was a monorail.
- Don't sit.

2386
01:19:20,640 --> 01:19:23,479
- An Ulsan resident said he saw it.
- He said he saw it.

2387
01:19:23,480 --> 01:19:24,939
I'm not from Nam-gu.

2388
01:19:24,940 --> 01:19:26,909
- There's something you can ride.
- You said you rode it.

2389
01:19:26,910 --> 01:19:28,449
Why did you say it with confidence?

2390
01:19:28,450 --> 01:19:29,719
I'm from Ulju-gun.

2391
01:19:29,720 --> 01:19:31,219
- This is ridiculous.
- You said you rode it.

2392
01:19:31,220 --> 01:19:32,679
- I...
- It isn't the aerial bicycle.

2393
01:19:32,680 --> 01:19:34,989
We have Korea's biggest swing.

2394
01:19:34,990 --> 01:19:37,260
- I think that's it.
- It's called the Whales Swing.

2395
01:19:37,720 --> 01:19:39,119
You said you rode it.

2396
01:19:39,120 --> 01:19:40,330
I thought I did.

2397
01:19:40,430 --> 01:19:42,289
At night, you can see the Ulsan Bridge.

